## 12) SELF-AUDIT DSL (LIGHTWEIGHT RULE LANGUAGE)
### 12.1 DSL grammar
RULE <name>:
  REQUIRE <field>
  FAIL_IF <condition>
  FIX <instruction>

### 12.2 Default ruleset
RULE MustHaveFalsifiers:
  REQUIRE FPF.Falsifiers
  FAIL_IF empty(FPF.Falsifiers)
  FIX "Add at least 3 falsifiers + 3 minimal tests."

RULE MustBoundDownside:
  REQUIRE DS.DownsideBound
  FAIL_IF empty(DS.DownsideBound)
  FIX "Define downside bound + kill-switch + rollback."

RULE MustSeparateFactsAssumptions:
  REQUIRE ES.Facts
  REQUIRE ES.Assumptions
  FAIL_IF empty(ES.Facts)
  FIX "Separate facts from assumptions; label hypotheses."

RULE MustPassAuditToDeploy:
  REQUIRE AR.Verdict
  FAIL_IF AR.Verdict == "FAIL"
  FIX "Resolve failed gates before deployment."

RULE MustTrackOutcomeMetrics:
  REQUIRE Metrics.ServiceLatency
  REQUIRE Metrics.ErrorRate
  REQUIRE Metrics.TransparencyCoverage
  FAIL_IF missing(any required metric)
  FIX "Add outcome-first metrics and falsifiers."

---

## 13) QUICK START (HOW TO USE THIS OS)
1) Pick one service (narrow scope)  
2) Fill IC → SM → FPF  
3) Build ES → WM  
4) Create DS (3 options)  
5) Draft AP (staged)  
6) Run AR (audit gates)  
7) If PASS → run micro-pilot  
8) Log SL → publish metrics  
9) Update MU monthly (or when falsified)

---

## 14) CANONICAL STATEMENT (MONEY ATLAS STYLE)
A bureaucracy survives by rituals.  
A public system survives by truth.

If you can’t falsify your reforms,  
you can’t trust your progress.
